# Exclude agent/harness state from `git archive` output — i.e. the source tarball the release workflow
# (.github/workflows/release.yml) attaches to a release. These are local tooling files, not engine source.
# Caveat: GitHub's automatically-attached "Source code (zip/tar.gz)" archives do not reliably honor
# export-ignore, so this guarantees only our explicit source archive is clean; to keep these out of every
# possible release bundle they would have to be untracked from the repo entirely.
.claude/ export-ignore
